<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="9" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName LSID="9521001C-4005-5F91-8123-0CE506FECCDB" authority="W. D. J. Koch, Syn. Fl. Germ. Helv., ed. 2. 190. 1843 [19 - 21 Jun 1843]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">Trifolium multistriatum W.D.J.Koch, Syn. Fl. Germ. Helv., ed. 2. 190. 1843 [19-21 Jun 1843]</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="9" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Type</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
(holotype indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Scoppola, A" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="275 - 281" refId="B50" refString="Scoppola, A, Lattanzi, E, 2016. Remarks on the type material and the identity of the name Trifoliummultistriatum W.D.J.Koch (T.vesiculosum-aggr., Fabaceae). Phytotaxa 277: 275 - 281" title="Remarks on the type material and the identity of the name Trifoliummultistriatum W. D. J. Koch (T. vesiculosum-aggr., Fabaceae)." volume="277" year="2016">Scoppola and Lattanzi 2016</bibRefCitation>
: 276). S. Andrea bey Triest, August 1840, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Tommasini</emphasis>
(L).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
Heads large; fruiting calyx ovoid with thick, longitudinal nerves all along, closed-spaced, transverse veins slightly visible; corolla&gt; than twice as long as the calyx tube, seeds ovoid, light brown and dark mottled (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Flowering head of Trifolium multistriatum from Seminara (Reggio Calabria) (Photo by L. Bernardo, 1 June 2016)." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106588" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure1">Figures 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Comparison between mature calyces of Trifolium subsect. Mystillus species in Italy (bar = 1 mm). Left: Trifolium vesiculosum (A) and Trifolium spumosum (A '), middle Trifolium multistriatum transitional (B) and typical (B ') forms, right Trifolium mutabile s. str. (C) and Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum (C ')." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106589" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2">2B</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Trifolium multistriatum, transitional forms (bar = 1 mm). Fresh flowers (24 June 2016) and seeds (5 August 2016) from plants collected in Rionero in Vulture (Potenza); detailed calyces from a specimen collected in the Ofanto valley (Aquilonia, Avellino) (CLU)." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106590" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure3">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Updated geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Friuli Venezia-Giulia: 0A, Liguria: 0A, Campania: + (new), Basilicata: + (new), Calabria: + (new), Sicily: - (new).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="10" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">
The identity and autonomy of the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="9">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
compared to the other species with whom it is closely related is discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Scoppola, A" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="275 - 281" refId="B50" refString="Scoppola, A, Lattanzi, E, 2016. Remarks on the type material and the identity of the name Trifoliummultistriatum W.D.J.Koch (T.vesiculosum-aggr., Fabaceae). Phytotaxa 277: 275 - 281" title="Remarks on the type material and the identity of the name Trifoliummultistriatum W. D. J. Koch (T. vesiculosum-aggr., Fabaceae)." volume="277" year="2016">Scoppola and Lattanzi (2016)</bibRefCitation>
. The original material (L!) was recorded in northern Italy during the second half of the nineteenth century and later disappeared. Its occurrence might be 
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="10" start="start">due</pageBreakToken>
to the transport of seeds by ship solid ballasts collected at the port of departure during the commercial activities of the Austrian Lloyd shipping company in the mid- to late-1800s (
<bibRefCitation author="Mack, RN" editor="Ruiz, GM" journalOrPublisher="Island Press, Washington" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="3 - 30" refId="B35" refString="Mack, RN, , 2004. Global plant dispersal, naturalization and invasion: pathways, modes and circumstances. In: Ruiz, GM, Carlton, JT, Eds., Invasive species: vectors and management strategies. Island Press, Washington: 3 - 30" title="Global plant dispersal, naturalization and invasion: pathways, modes and circumstances." volumeTitle="Invasive species: vectors and management strategies" year="2004">Mack 2004</bibRefCitation>
). In BEOU, FI, PAD and TSM, there is evidence of the presence of the species at that time also in Dalmatia, Albania and Montenegro (
<bibRefCitation author="Visiani, R de" journalOrPublisher="Friedrich Hofmeister, Leipzig" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="289 - 300" refId="B58" refString="Visiani, R de, 1852. Flora Dalmatica sive enumeratio stirpium vascularium quas hactenus in Dalmatia lectas et sibi observatas descripsit, digessit rariorumque iconibus illustravit. Friedrich Hofmeister, Leipzig: 289 - 300" title="Flora Dalmatica sive enumeratio stirpium vascularium quas hactenus in Dalmatia lectas et sibi observatas descripsit, digessit rariorumque iconibus illustravit" year="1852">Visiani 1852</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Nyman, CF" journalOrPublisher="Orebro Sueciae" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.10533" refId="B43" refString="Nyman, CF, 1878. Conspectus Florae Europaeae. Orebro Sueciae, 177 pp." title="Conspectus Florae Europaeae" url="10.5962/bhl.title.10533" year="1878">Nyman 1878</bibRefCitation>
). Specimens at MPU were collected in 1831, 1851 and 1858 at 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Port-Juvénal">Port-Juvenal</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hérault">Herault</normalizedToken>
(southern France), where 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vesiculosum" variety="rumelicum">Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum</taxonomicName>
Griseb.) is considered as a historical alien species (
<bibRefCitation author="Coulot, P" journalOrPublisher="Societe Botanique du Centre-Ouest, Jarnac" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B10" refString="Coulot, P, Rabaute, P, 2013. Monographie des Leguminosae de France. Tome 3. Tribu des Trifolieae. Societe Botanique du Centre-Ouest, Jarnac" title="Monographie des Leguminosae de France. Tome 3. Tribu des Trifolieae." year="2013">Coulot and Rabaute 2013</bibRefCitation>
) as in Austria and Switzerland (
<bibRefCitation author="Gams, H" editor="Hegi, G" journalOrPublisher="Illustrierte Flora von Mittel-Europa" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B19" refString="Gams, H, Hegi, G, 1923. Genus Trifolium. Illustrierte Flora von Mittel-Europa 4, 1280 pp." title="Genus Trifolium." volume="4" year="1923">Gams 1923</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller 1984</bibRefCitation>
). Even 
<bibRefCitation author="Fiori, A" journalOrPublisher="Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="859 - 860" refId="B17" refString="Fiori, A, 1925. . Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia 1: 859 - 860" volume="1" year="1925">Fiori (1925)</bibRefCitation>
lists the species for Liguria as sub 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum var. multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vesiculosum" variety="multistriatum">Trifolium vesiculosum var. multistriatum</taxonomicName>
W.D.J.Koch, writing: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“È">&quot;E</normalizedToken>
stato osservato avvent. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="…">...</normalizedToken>
in Lig. ma a quanto pare vi 
<normalizedToken originalValue="è">e</normalizedToken>
scomparso&quot;. According to the above, the report appears plausible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="11" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">
The delimitation, status and distribution of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with respect to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium setiferum" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setiferum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="10">Trifolium setiferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="10" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="vesiculosum" variety="rumelicum">Trifolium vesiculosum var. rumelicum</taxonomicName>
, is still under debate (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B25" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist 4. Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" title="Med-Checklist 4." year="1989">Greuter et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ellison, NW" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" publicationUrl="http://ww2.bgbm.org/EuroPlusMed/" refId="B15" refString="2006 onwards. Euro+Med PlantBase-the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity.http://ww2.bgbm.org/EuroPlusMed/" title="Euro + Med PlantBase-the information resource for Euro-Mediterranean plant diversity" url="http://ww2.bgbm.org/EuroPlusMed/" year="2006 onwards">Euro+Med 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Scoppola, A" editor="Peruzzi, L" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" publicationUrl="10.11646/phytotaxa.277.3.5" refId="B49" refString="Scoppola, A, Lattanzi, E, Peruzzi, L, Domina, G, 2015. Gruppo per la Floristica, Sistematica ed Evoluzione della Societa Botanica Italiana, Palermo.10.11646/phytotaxa.277.3.5" title="Gruppo per la Floristica, Sistematica ed Evoluzione della Societa Botanica Italiana, Palermo" url="10.11646/phytotaxa.277.3.5" year="2015">Scoppola and Lattanzi 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Scoppola, A" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" pagination="275 - 281" refId="B50" refString="Scoppola, A, Lattanzi, E, 2016. Remarks on the type material and the identity of the name Trifoliummultistriatum W.D.J.Koch (T.vesiculosum-aggr., Fabaceae). Phytotaxa 277: 275 - 281" title="Remarks on the type material and the identity of the name Trifoliummultistriatum W. D. J. Koch (T. vesiculosum-aggr., Fabaceae)." volume="277" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
). Here we confirm the 
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="11" start="start">historical</pageBreakToken>
populations of Basilicata and Calabria (
<bibRefCitation author="Fiori, A" journalOrPublisher="Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="859 - 860" refId="B17" refString="Fiori, A, 1925. . Nuova Flora Analitica d'Italia 1: 859 - 860" volume="1" year="1925">Fiori 1925</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gavioli, O" journalOrPublisher="Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (nuova serie)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="134 - 135" refId="B20" refString="Gavioli, O, 1948. Synopsis Florae Lucanae. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (nuova serie) 54: 134 - 135" title="Synopsis Florae Lucanae." volume="54" year="1948">Gavioli 1948</bibRefCitation>
) and add a new locality in Campania. The presence in Campania at the foothills of the Vesuvius (RO!) was not confirmed either by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ricciardi, M" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="3 - 121" refId="B48" refString="Ricciardi, M, Aprile, GG, La Valva, V, Caputo, G, 1986. La Flora del Somma-Vesuvio. Bollettino della Societa dei Naturalisti in Napoli 96: 3 - 121" title="La Flora del Somma-Vesuvio." volume="96" year="1986">Ricciardi et al. (1986)</bibRefCitation>
nor by our own research. However, the discovery in 2015 of a native population of the species in the Ofanto valley (Aquilonia, Avellino) has confirmed its occurrence in Campania. 
<bibRefCitation author="Gavioli, O" journalOrPublisher="Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (nuova serie)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="134 - 135" refId="B20" refString="Gavioli, O, 1948. Synopsis Florae Lucanae. Nuovo Giornale Botanico Italiano (nuova serie) 54: 134 - 135" title="Synopsis Florae Lucanae." volume="54" year="1948">Gavioli (1948)</bibRefCitation>
collected the species in Basilicata in 1939 in the historical locality of Mt. Vulture, already known to Fiori (FI!). We also found it around the lakes of Monticchio and at San Michele (Rionero in Vulture), even at the edges of resting fields. We cannot exclude the presence of transitional forms towards 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium vesiculosum" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vesiculosum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="11">Trifolium vesiculosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, already assumed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibelli, G" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="179 - 222" refId="B23" refString="Gibelli, G, Belli, S, 1892. Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p.p.). Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2) 42: 179 - 222" title="Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p. p.)." volume="42" year="1892">Gibelli and Belli (1892)</bibRefCitation>
in this area (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Trifolium multistriatum, transitional forms (bar = 1 mm). Fresh flowers (24 June 2016) and seeds (5 August 2016) from plants collected in Rionero in Vulture (Potenza); detailed calyces from a specimen collected in the Ofanto valley (Aquilonia, Avellino) (CLU)." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106590" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure3">Figure 3</figureCitation>
). We also confirm the Calabrian historical localities where the species is locally abundant; some populations, still under study, show longitudinal calyx nerves that are more prominent and often in greater number and a less swollen calyx (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Comparison between mature calyces of Trifolium subsect. Mystillus species in Italy (bar = 1 mm). Left: Trifolium vesiculosum (A) and Trifolium spumosum (A '), middle Trifolium multistriatum transitional (B) and typical (B ') forms, right Trifolium mutabile s. str. (C) and Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum (C ')." figureDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/106589" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" tableDoi="10.3897/italianbotanist.2.10361.figure2">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
'), which are not typical for 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium multistriatum" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multistriatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="11">Trifolium multistriatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boissier, E" journalOrPublisher="H. Georg, Basilea" pageId="12" pageNumber="19" pagination="110 - 156" publicationUrl="10.5962/bhl.title.20323" refId="B2" refString="Boissier, E, 1872. Flora Orientalis. H. Georg, Basilea: 110 - 156" title="Flora Orientalis" url="10.5962/bhl.title.20323" year="1872">Boissier 1872</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibelli, G" journalOrPublisher="Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2)" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="179 - 222" refId="B23" refString="Gibelli, G, Belli, S, 1892. Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p.p.). Memorie della Reale accademia delle scienze di Torino (serie 2) 42: 179 - 222" title="Rivista critica delle specie di Trifolium italiane comparate con quelle del resto d'Europa e delle regioni circummediterranee della sezione Trigantheum Nobis (Mistyllus Presl. p. p.)." volume="42" year="1892">Gibelli and Belli 1892</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hossain, M" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" pagination="387 - 481" refId="B29" refString="Hossain, M, 1961. A revision of Trifolium in the Nearer East. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 23: 387 - 481" title="A revision of Trifolium in the Nearer East." volume="23" year="1961">Hossain 1961</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zohary, M" journalOrPublisher="The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" pageId="15" pageNumber="22" refId="B62" refString="Zohary, M, Heller, D, 1984. The Genus Trifolium. The Israel Academy of Sciences and Humanities, Jerusalem" title="The Genus Trifolium." year="1984">Zohary and Heller 1984</bibRefCitation>
). We also found transitional forms towards 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mutabile" variety="gussoneanum">Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum</taxonomicName>
Gibelli &amp; Belli, a variety already known for Sicily (
<bibRefCitation author="Giardina, G" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="181 - 182" refId="B22" refString="Giardina, G, Raimondo, F, Spadaro, V, 2007. A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily. Bocconea 20: 181 - 182" title="A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily." volume="20" year="2007">Giardina et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="La Rosa, A" journalOrPublisher="Universita degli Studi di Palermo" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B30" refString="La Rosa, A, 2011. Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia. Universita degli Studi di Palermo" title="Indagini tassonomiche, ecologiche e distributive sul genere Trifolium L. in Sicilia" year="2011">La Rosa 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and confirmed by our study in Calabria, that deserves further investigation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="11">
The sole report of this species from Sicily (provisionally treated as 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium setiferum" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="setiferum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="11">Trifolium setiferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Greuter, W" journalOrPublisher="Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B25" refString="Greuter, W, Burdet, HM, Long, G, 1989. Med-Checklist 4. Conservatoire et Jardin Botaniques, Geneve" title="Med-Checklist 4." year="1989">Greuter et al. 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Conti, F" journalOrPublisher="Palombi Editori, Roma" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" refId="B8" refString="Conti, F, Abbate, G, Alessandrini, A, Blasi, C, 2005. An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora. Palombi Editori, Roma" title="An annotated checklist of the Italian vascular flora." year="2005">Conti et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Giardina, G" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="181 - 182" refId="B22" refString="Giardina, G, Raimondo, F, Spadaro, V, 2007. A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily. Bocconea 20: 181 - 182" title="A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily." volume="20" year="2007">Giardina et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) is based on an old record &quot;Castellammare, Todaro (sine indicatione nominis ac loci typici)
<normalizedToken originalValue="….”">....&quot;</normalizedToken>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lojacono Pojero, M" journalOrPublisher="Palermo" pageId="14" pageNumber="21" refId="B32" refString="Lojacono Pojero, M, 1909. Flora Sicula. Palermo, 437 pp." title="Flora Sicula" year="1909">Lojacono (1909)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Giardina, G" journalOrPublisher="Bocconea" pageId="13" pageNumber="20" pagination="181 - 182" refId="B22" refString="Giardina, G, Raimondo, F, Spadaro, V, 2007. A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily. Bocconea 20: 181 - 182" title="A catalogue of plants growing in Sicily." volume="20" year="2007">Giardina et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
do not confirm its autonomy; in addition, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Todaro’s">Todaro's</normalizedToken>
alleged sample, who reports the location Castellana, and not Castellammare (PAL!), is undoubtedly to be referred to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trifolium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum" order="Fabales" pageId="4" pageNumber="11" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="mutabile" variety="gussoneanum">Trifolium mutabile var. gussoneanum</taxonomicName>
. In the absence of clear references and specimens, we prefer not to confirm the presence of this species in Sicily.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
